The paper deals with improving the performance of deep convolutional neural networks on image classification tasks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the challenges of training very deep models, which is a topic in neural networks (cs.NE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper proposes a modification to the activation function used in residual networks, which is a topic in natural language processing (cs.CL) as well.
